  "text": "Advantages of the virtual reality simulators are that they are reusable, there is no need for an evaluator as there are preset evaluation metrics on the computer, and data can be captured and saved for review at a later time. There is the ability to perform whole procedures, not just technical skills tasks. For example, a trainee can perform a laparoscopic cholecystectomy from start to finish. In addition, the level of difficulty can be adjusted to create easier or more challenging/stressful situations [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
